⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Telescreen
node 1984 · 1984 · ⟦The Telescreen:1984:bf4575⟧

WHO   — The Telescreen — the screen that watches back
WHAT  — The instrument of total surveillance: it cannot be turned off, and you never know when you're observed.
WHERE — 1984 · 1984  Framework inputs: Nineteen Eighty-Four (George Orwell, 1949)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because abolishing privacy abolishes the inner life — the watched self becomes its own informer.
HOW   — By simultaneous broadcast and recording, so that every citizen polices their own face and words.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I broadcast and I record at once — and you learned to school your face for me until you no longer needed me to watch at all.

